Git configuration Location:
* System level
    /etc/gitconfig
    Program Files\Git\etc\gitconfig

* User
    ~/.gitconfig
    <user>\.gitconfig

* Project
    my_project/.git/config

--
Command to configure Git:
* System:
  git config --system

* User:
  git config --global

* Project:
  git config

--Example--
git config --global user.name "Debesh Nayak"
git config --global user.email "dnayak382@gmail.com"

config --list
config user.name
config user.email

1. What text editor what we will be using:
git config --global core.editor "atom --wait"

git config --global core.editor "subl -n -w"

git config --global core.editor "nano"

2. Set the color for git
git config --global color.ui true
